Menu

 
 





The aVAD™ is a new intraventricular heart pump which is small outside at 2.48 centimeters in diameter and big inside with a 1.2 centimeter diameter flow tube.  
The intraventricular implant of the aVAD™ may facilitate a less invasive surgical technique. 
The aVAD™ has CE Mark approval for distribution in Europe. In the United States, the aVAD™ is in preclinical testing and is expected to enter a short/long FDA IDE trial in 2017. 








ReliantHeart’s aVAD CE Mark awarded August 2, 2016

 
 



Comparison of popular LVADs

The HeartAssist5® includes features such as FlowAccurate™ Diagnostics,  HeartAssistRemote™ Monitoring and INR Tracking. These exclusive features are available only with the HeartAssist5®.
Read more


FlowAccurate™ Diagnostics

The HeartAssist5® takes the guesswork out of patient care management. The HeartAssist5®  is the only device that precisely measures blood flow, speed and power, alerting clinicians to potential issues.
Read more


HeartAssistRemote™

HeartAssist5® Patients can feel more secure about their heart health while enjoying life at home or traveling, with HeartAssistRemote™  Monitoring which continuously transmits patient data to expert clinicians  via VADLink.com.
Read more


